sql:
SELECT AVG(life_expectancy) AS average_life_expectancy
FROM life_expectancy
WHERE year = 2009;

external_knowledge:
- Health indicators and economic indicators are metrics used to measure the health and economic performance of countries; 
- Income groups are categories that classify countries based on their economic performance; 
- Regions are geographical areas that group countries together; 
- Access logs track user interactions with data; 
- Data validation ensures the accuracy of the data.

- Top-performing countries refers to those with life expectancy exceeding the average of their region and income group, and being ranked within the top three in their region and income group; 
- Regional average and income group average refer to the mean life expectancy of countries within the same region or income group, respectively; 
- Rank is determined by the life expectancy of countries in descending order within each region and income group.

sql:
SELECT income_group_name, AVG(gdp_per_capita) AS average_gdp_per_capita
FROM income_groups
GROUP BY income_group_name;

SELECT income_group_name, MAX(gdp_per_capita) AS max_gdp_per_capita
FROM income_groups
WHERE income_group_id = 1;
